title: Import NZ Freshwater Fish datasets. — nzffdr_import
text: institution institution collected data. Use nzffdr_get_table("institution") function see list possible options, set arg want institutions database. catchment_num catchment number. 6 digit number unique reach interest. can search using individual number (e.g. catchment = "702.500"), rivers catchment can use wildcard search term (e.g. catchment = "702%"), set arg want catchments database. catchment_name catchment name. e.g. catchment_name = "Hinds R".  Case sensitive. set arg want catchments database. water_body water body name. e.g. get records Limestone Creek, water_body = "Limestone Creek". set arg want water bodies database. fish_method fishing method used. Use nzffdr_get_table("fish_method")  function see list possible options. want fish caught lures use fish_meth = "Angling - Lure", set arg want fishing methods database. taxon taxon interest. Use nzffdr_get_table("taxon") function see list possible options. can search using either  common scientific names can search multiple taxon  , e.g. search Black mudfish use taxon = "Black mudfish"  taxon = "Neochanna diversus" search Black mudfish Bluegill bully use taxon = c("Black mudfish", "Bluegill bully")  etc. starts start year. set arg want records database. ends end year. set arg want records database. download_format use "" "essential" download either,  variables (67 columns), now includes River Environment Classification data, just essential data (23 columns).
